        <section class="detail-section alt"><div class="detail-shell"><header class="detail-heading detail-reveal"><small>Reflection</small><h2>Researching across technical and human perspectives.</h2></header><div class="reflection detail-reveal">I chose this topic because DRM sits at the intersection of information security, copyright, platform economics, privacy, and ethics. The main challenge was comparing legal, technical, user, and creator perspectives without treating any single viewpoint as complete. Screening sources, extracting themes, comparing disagreements, and checking citations strengthened my critical analysis and synthesis. Future work could add interviews with artists and listeners, compare additional streaming platforms, and evaluate newer transparency and privacy practices.</div><nav class="project-pagination" aria-label="Project navigation"><a href="web-development.html"><small>Previous project</small>100SMILES Dental Care Website</a><a class="all-projects" href="index.html#projects">Back to all projects</a><a href="technology-literature-review.html"><small>Next project</small>Technology Literature Review</a></nav></div></section>
